Process called "translate_logical_expr" takes context as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate logical expression to HIR

    Let hir be proc create_dictionary from Dict

    proc set_dict_string_value from Dict with hir, "_type", "cobol_logical_expr"

    Return hir
End Process

Process called "translate_figurative_const" takes context as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate figurative constant to HIR

    @Reasoning:
    Figurative constants: ZERO, SPACES, HIGH-VALUES, LOW-VALUES, etc.
    Translate to HIR special constants.
    @End Reasoning

    Let hir be proc create_dictionary from Dict

    proc set_dict_string_value from Dict with hir, "_type", "cobol_figurative_constant"

    Let name be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 8
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc set_dict_string_value from Dict with hir, "constant", name
    End If

    Return hir
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Utility Functions
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "translate_children" takes context as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Translate all children of node to HIR list

    @Reasoning:
    Common pattern: translate all child nodes and return as HIR list.
    @End Reasoning

    Let result be proc create_list from ListOps

    Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 24
    Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 32
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than child_count:
        Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, i times 8
        Let child_hir be proc translate_node from context, child

        If child_hir is not equal to 0:
            proc list_append from ListOps with result, child_hir
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Return result
End Process

Note: End of COBOL to HIR Translator
